Worked Solution

To find the inverse of the function \( \displaystyle R(x) = {@rx@}\), we'll follow these steps:

1. Replace \(R(x)\) with \(y\): \( \displaystyle {@x_eq@}\).

2. Swap the roles of \(x\) and \(y\): \( \displaystyle {@y_eq@}\).

3. We solve the resulting equation for \(y\) to get \(R^{-1}(x)\).

\(\displaystyle {@y_eq@} \\ {@(denom(rhs(y_eq)))*x@}= {@num(rhs(y_eq))@} \\ {@expand((denom(rhs(y_eq)))*x)@}= {@num(rhs(y_eq))@} \\ \displaystyle {@solutions[1]@}\)

Now, we have \(\displaystyle R^{-1}(x) = {@y_solved@}\).

Please note that for the inverse to be valid, the original function \(R(x)\) must be one-to-one (bijective), meaning that each value of \(x\) corresponds to a unique value of \(y\), and vice versa.

If the original function is not one-to-one, its inverse might not exist.

When calculating the inverse of a function \(R(x)\) we are finding a new function that will tell us which \(x\) value will give as a particular \(y\) value when we input it in \(R\). Therefore, in the case of \(R(x)={@(aa*x+bb)/(cc*x+dd)@}\), we write it as \(y={@(aa*x+bb)/(cc*x+dd)@}\) and invert the variables \(x\) and \(y\) to get \(x={@(aa*y+bb)/(cc*y+dd)@}\) and rearrange as follows:

\[x={@(aa*y+bb)/(cc*y+dd)@}\]

\[x\cdot ({@cc*y+dd@})={@aa*y+bb@}\]

\[{@cc*y*x+dd*x@}={@aa*y+bb@}\]

\[{@cc*y*x-aa*y@}={@bb-dd*x@}\]
\[{@y*(cc*x-aa)@}={@bb-dd*x@}\]
\[{@y@}={@(bb-dd*x)/(cc*x-aa)@}\]
The inverse of \(R(x)\) is therefore \(R^{-1}(x) = {@(bb-dd*x)/(cc*x-aa)@}\).
